<li id="cite_note-25"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Baron, <i>Brewed in America</i>, 74.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Wells, <i>Life and Public Services</i>, 1:24.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-27"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-27">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Baron, <i>Brewed in America</i>, 74–75; Alexander, <i>Revolutionary Politician</i>, 231. However, Stoll (<i>Samuel Adams</i>, 275n16) notes that <a href="../../w/index-title=James_Koch&action=edit&redlink=1.php.html" class="new" title="James Koch (page does not exist)">James Koch</a>, founder of the <a href="Boston_Beer_Company" title="Boston Beer Company" class="mw-redirect">Boston Beer Company</a>, reports having seen a receipt for <a href="Hops" title="Hops">hops</a> signed by Adams, which indicates that Adams may have done some brewing.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-28"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Miller, <i>Pioneer</i>, 17–18; Alexander, <i>Revolutionary Politician</i>, 7.</span></li>
